{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-bede23a5bc7eff44", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# HiFi-Codec: Group-residual Vector quantization for High Fidelity Audio Codec\narXiv: 2305.02765\nAuthors: Dongchao Yang, Songxiang Liu, Rongjie Huang, Jinchuan Tian, Chao Weng, Yuexian Zou\nYear: 2023 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Proposal of a group-residual vector quantization (GRVQ) technique that splits latent features into groups and applies residual vector quantization to each group independently.\n  2. Development of HiFi-Codec, a high-fidelity audio codec model utilizing GRVQ that achieves better reconstruction performance than Encodec while requiring only four codebooks.\n  3. Introduction of AcademiCodec, the first open-source audio codec toolkit providing training codes and pre-trained models for Encodec, SoundStream, and HiFi-Codec.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/量化-RVQ, 压缩/语义声学-声学\n===\n# U-Codec: Ultra Low Frame-rate Neural Speech Codec for Fast High-fidelity Speech Generation\narXiv: 2510.16718\nAuthors: Xusheng Yang, Long Zhou, Wenfu Wang, Kai Hu, Shulin Feng, Chenxing Li, Meng Yu, Dong Yu, Yuexian Zou\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present U-Codec, the first ultra low frame-rate speech codec that operates at 5Hz with extreme compression to provide a discrete speech tokenizer for efficient LLM-based systems.\n  2. We systematically optimize residual vector quantization (RVQ) depth and codebook size, and introduce a Transformer-based inter-frame dependency module to preserve intelligibility and spectral detail under extreme compression.\n  3. We introduce a Codecformer network with global and local hierarchical architecture to reduce the cost of TTS inference while maintaining scalability to deeper RVQ stacks.\n  4. Comprehensive evaluations show that U-Codec improves LLM-based TTS inference speed by about 3 times compared with high-frame-rate codecs while maintaining state-of-the-art quality.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/量化-RVQ, TTS, TTS/功能-快速生成\n===\n# HH-Codec: High Compression High-fidelity Discrete Neural Codec for Spoken Language Modeling\narXiv: 2507.18897\nAuthors: Rongkun Xue, Yazhe Niu, Shuai Hu, Zixin Yin, Yongqiang Yao, Jing Yang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce a discrete neural codec that achieves excellent speech reconstruction with the lowest cost—24 tokens for 24 kHz audio at a just 0.3 kbps bandwidth.\n  2. We design a speech-specific SLM-VQ that incorporates an asymmetric architecture, significantly enhancing stability and performance under high compression conditions.\n  3. Experiments show that HH-Codec performs on par with several leading speech tokenizers across various datasets, while ablations confirm the necessity of each component and validate its potential for spoken language modeling.\n\nTags: 压缩/量化-VQ, 压缩/量化-RVQ, 压缩/语义声学-混合", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "ec06fbc6-a26f-45e6-9ef0-44ed455875f4", "uuid": "50a38be3-b21f-4154-a1c4-2df13fdc9143", "timestamp": "2026-07-21T10:54:33.686Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# HiFi-Codec: Group-residual Vector quantization for High Fidelity Audio Codec\narXiv: 2305.02765\nAuthors: Dongchao Yang, Songxiang Liu, Rongjie Huang, Jinchuan Tian, Chao Weng, Yuexian Zou\nYear: 2023 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Proposal of a group-residual vector quantization (GRVQ) technique that splits latent features into groups and applies residual vector quantization to each group independently.\n  2. Development of HiFi-Codec, a high-fidelity audio codec model utilizing GRVQ that achieves better reconstruction performance than Encodec while requiring only four codebooks.\n  3. Introduction of AcademiCodec, the first open-source audio codec toolkit providing training codes and pre-trained models for Encodec, SoundStream, and HiFi-Codec.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/量化-RVQ, 压缩/语义声学-声学\n===\n# U-Codec: Ultra Low Frame-rate Neural Speech Codec for Fast High-fidelity Speech Generation\narXiv: 2510.16718\nAuthors: Xusheng Yang, Long Zhou, Wenfu Wang, Kai Hu, Shulin Feng, Chenxing Li, Meng Yu, Dong Yu, Yuexian Zou\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We present U-Codec, the first ultra low frame-rate speech codec that operates at 5Hz with extreme compression to provide a discrete speech tokenizer for efficient LLM-based systems.\n  2. We systematically optimize residual vector quantization (RVQ) depth and codebook size, and introduce a Transformer-based inter-frame dependency module to preserve intelligibility and spectral detail under extreme compression.\n  3. We introduce a Codecformer network with global and local hierarchical architecture to reduce the cost of TTS inference while maintaining scalability to deeper RVQ stacks.\n  4. Comprehensive evaluations show that U-Codec improves LLM-based TTS inference speed by about 3 times compared with high-frame-rate codecs while maintaining state-of-the-art quality.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/量化-RVQ, TTS, TTS/功能-快速生成\n===\n# HH-Codec: High Compression High-fidelity Discrete Neural Codec for Spoken Language Modeling\narXiv: 2507.18897\nAuthors: Rongkun Xue, Yazhe Niu, Shuai Hu, Zixin Yin, Yongqiang Yao, Jing Yang\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. We introduce a discrete neural codec that achieves excellent speech reconstruction with the lowest cost—24 tokens for 24 kHz audio at a just 0.3 kbps bandwidth.\n  2. We design a speech-specific SLM-VQ that incorporates an asymmetric architecture, significantly enhancing stability and performance under high compression conditions.\n  3. Experiments show that HH-Codec performs on par with several leading speech tokenizers across various datasets, while ablations confirm the necessity of each component and validate its potential for spoken language modeling.\n\nTags: 压缩/量化-VQ, 压缩/量化-RVQ, 压缩/语义声学-混合", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
